## Probe Output Bug

Problem found:

scripts/probe-native-poller.mjs returned from the no-trigger-created branch before the final JSON print and process-exit classification. That could make a failed probe look like exit 0 with empty output.

Change:

The no-trigger-created branch now sets result fields and falls through to the common JSON print and exit-code logic.

Verification command:

node scripts/probe-native-poller.mjs --watch-seconds 10 --hash T5L_PROBE_NO_TRIGGER_PRINT_FIX_20260523T1408Z

Result:

exit=2
hash=T5L_PROBE_NO_TRIGGER_PRINT_FIX_20260523T1408Z
bridge_mode=stopped_for_native_probe
message=04eff93f-973e-4ab2-be37-08c3e533e286
trigger=9ee1bfbe-8364-4792-bd58-a07a144b52dd
final_claimed_at=null
final_completed_at=null
ack_rows=[]
bridge_assisted_pass=false
native_pass=false
verdict=native_poller_still_blocked

The fixed probe prints JSON and exits nonzero when native activation fails.

